comment: up to 70 during ferm, still ice bathing
4.25 2 row .75 tipple blend, 4 vienna 1 wheat (both german)
wanted to use tettnager, couldnt get it, had to sub in with what i have
so 1.045 to 1.000 for 6%, very nice, spicy, dry and a little bitterness to round out the phenolics
finished at 1.000 or 1.001, crazy low, seems too low, smelled fantastic, spicy!
actually a bit too dry, id mash a bit hotter and go with all vienna for the base

i love the spiciness of the yeast and sweetness of the malt and yeast combo, a touch bitter for this low an FG, mash at 158 next time for this same recipe and maybe a touch lower IBUs. really pleasant and deceptively strong for such a dry, seemingly light beer
id consider increasing the vienna next time as well
